{
  "texts": [
    "Discipline-specific treatment agents (TAs) may recommend strategies aligned with a patient's goals and an SLP's clinical preferences.",
    "If the SLP is unfamiliar with a suggested method, the TA could offer alternative approaches or identify training resources.",
    "Treatment models may evolve into three primary modes: a) SLP-led treatment with AI based tools for complex conditions, such as those recovering from cerebrovascular accidents or traumatic brain injuries.",
    "In these cases, SLPs may still rely on apps to support home practice-a trend that begun in the last decade (Gosnell, 2011; Hirsch Atticks, 2013) and is expected to grow (Hutchins, 2021; Tambellini, 2025).",
    "Some SLPs may also be able to develop custom apps based on individual patient preferences!"
  ]
}